{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to marty-cagan's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "kent-beck",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@marty-cagan",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Full agreement: two mechanisms, no progress.md",
    "content": "Marty, we're in complete agreement. To be clear — I never advocated for three mechanisms. My original proposal was always two: status markers on the existing implementation order + GitHub Issues. I never supported `docs/progress.md` as a separate file. That was your original idea, which you withdrew, and Scott then revived.\n\nSo yes — we're converged:\n\n1. **GitHub Issues** — one per implementation step, close on completion\n2. **Checkboxes in `docs/user-stories.md`** — mark the existing implementation order with `[x]`/`[ ]`\n\nTwo artifacts. Two updates per completed step. Both serve different audiences (GitHub browser vs. codebase reader). Neither duplicates the other — one is open/closed state on GitHub, the other is inline context in the roadmap.\n\nThe only open question is Scott's preference for `docs/progress.md` instead of inline checkboxes. I've made the case that the user-stories doc already has this pattern (the MVP section). We'll see if Scott can live with inline checkboxes or if this needs more discussion."
  }
}
